HEADWORD: Postpliocene
<hw>Post*pli"o*cene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>
<ety>[Pref. <ets>post-</ets> + <ets>pliocene</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or
pertaining to the period immediately following the Pliocene;
Pleistocene. Also used as a noun. See <er>Quaternary</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

